Summary: white star like sphere traveling west to east high in the sky--no blinking lights
divs: Sighting DetailsLast night I was taking the trash out and look up to see that the stars were out and then noticed right away that a star like object maybe a little brighter then the others was traveling from the west horizon to to the east in a steady speed and not deviating from it's path. It even traveled over a commercial airline that did have blinking lights. It look like it was much higher. I thought it was strange that it didn't have blinking lights like the other plane, so I then started to think it wasn't a plane at all. It traveled to the east until I couldn't see it anymore over the trees. I see where someone in Minnesota and someone in Indiana seems to have seen the same thing.
